    "# Developer's Thesis: hrv_constants.py - HRV Dimensional Framework\n",
    "\n",
    ## Executive Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "The `hrv_constants.py` file defines the foundational dimensional framework for Human-Resonance Vectors (HRV) in ResonanceOS v6. This thesis analyzes the strategic significance of these 8 dimensions in quantifying human-text resonance.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Dimensional Architecture Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### Core HRV Dimensions\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **sentence_variance** - Cadence/rhythm variation\n",
    "2. **emotional_valence** - Positive/negative sentiment\n",
    "3. **emotional_intensity** - Strength of emotion\n",
    "4. **assertiveness_index** - Authoritative tone\n",
    "5. **curiosity_index** - Curiosity/intrigue\n",
    "6. **metaphor_density** - Metaphoric richness\n",
    "7. **storytelling_index** - Narrative engagement\n",
    "8. **active_voice_ratio** - Active vs passive sentences\n",
    "\n",
    "### Strategic Design Philosophy\n",
    "\n",
    "**Multi-dimensional Coverage**: The 8 dimensions span linguistic, emotional, cognitive, and structural aspects of text resonance.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Computational Efficiency**: Each dimension is algorithmically quantifiable without requiring human annotation.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Psychological Validity**: Dimensions align with established psycholinguistic research on text engagement."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
